<HEADLINE>
SOWARD'S COMMENTS SPICE UP TROJANS' BYE WEEK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ In an otherwise tranquil bye week for USC, wide
receiver R. Jay Soward has managed to keep things interesting.
Again.
</P>
<P>
   During an interview in the summer with this week's ESPN
magazine, Soward vented on a couple of notable subjects, including
USC coach Paul Hackett.
</P>
<P>
   Soward accused Hackett of spying on him, saying ``Hackett wants
to know everything. He even has people that sit in our parties.
That's why I don't hang at 'SC.''
</P>
<P>
   Soward did not back off those comments when asked to verify
them.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's a lot that goes on here,'' Soward said. ``(But) I'm
happy it's in ESPN and not the newspapers.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett was amused by Soward's charges in the article.
</P>
<P>
   ``I would say that's a figment of his imagination,'' Hackett
said. ``I told R. Jay before the season, that he underestimates the
number of people who see him and know what's going on in this
city.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett is more interested in Soward having a good senior season
than rehashing any previous issues.
</P>
<P>
   ``He needs to perform. He seems to be at the top of his game
right now,'' Hackett said. ``Can he finish (his season) off
(strong) and catapult us? That's what it's all about.''
</P>
<P>
   Soward also had some terse comments over his rocky relationship
with former USC wide receiver Keyshawn Johnson, who plays for the
New York Jets. Soward has suspected that Johnson wanted him to sign
with Johnson's agent, and had an expletive-filled response to
Johnson's advice that he abandon his rap music career and worry
only about football.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's mean to me,'' Soward said. ``But I love the guy.''
</P>
<P>
   Pierson questionable: Freshman fullback Chad Pierson, who
sprained his ankle against Hawaii, might be able to play against
San Diego State, Hackett said. When the Trojans return to practice
Sunday, cornerback Kevin Arbet (ankle), linebacker Jason Steen
(neck) and offensive lineman Trevor Roberts (ankle) are still
expected to be out.
</P>
<P>
   Day off: USC takes today off, then resumes practice Sunday
night. Most of the coaches are busy this weekend, attending high
school games Friday night and junior-college games today.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
