<HEADLINE>
HOW-TO-SLEEP BOOKS: TO READ, PERCHANCE TO DROOL ON YOUR PILLOW 
</HEADLINE>
  (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact Olivia Vasquez in Los
Angeles (Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
 (bl)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Sleep, while never exactly out of style, seems really in vogue
now. The Wall Street Journal this year proclaimed it ``the new
status symbol.'' Business superstars like Jeff Bezos of Amazon.com
and Marc Andreesen of Netscape _ in contrast with past
overachievers like Thomas Edison, who scoffed at sleep _ brag about
