   GATES-SENIOR-PROFILE (Seattle) _ Profile of William Gates Sr.,
Bill Gates's father, who will run the Bill-and-Melinda Gates
Foundation, the nation's largest philanthropic foundation, which is
soon to be the world's largest as well. By Sam Howe Verhovek.
</P>
<P>
   With photo and graphic.
</P>
<P>
   AFTER-CANOSA (Miami) _ Two years after the death of the
undisputed leader of Cuban Americans in Miami, no single leader has
emerged. No one has Jorge Mas Canosa's charisma, influence and ties
to Washington. Besides, the Cuban American population, dominant in
South Florida, no longer speaks with one voice, nor is it
controlled by any single viewpoint. By Rick Bragg.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   FORD-POLLUTION-FIGHT (Detroit) _ Mark Pickrell used to be a
lawyer for Big Tobacco. Now he's representing a one-man Internet
site against Ford, and contends that the auto industry's handling
of sport utility vehicles' air pollution and poor fuel economy is
just like the tobacco industry's handling of smoking issues. Ralph
Nader agrees, and has coincidentally asked the Justice Department
to reopen an antitrust investigation from the 1960s into whether
Detroit colludes not to put advanced pollution-control equipment on
automobiles. By Keith Bradsher.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   (Coded w)
