<P>
   SUV-PROBLEM (Los Angeles) _ Sport-utility vehicles _ those
rolling behemoths with armored bumpers and beefy tires _ are built
to conquer wide open spaces. But often all they conquer are parking
spaces _ many too small to fit SUVs and pickup trucks. Finally,
parking experts are starting to listen. As sales of SUVs and pickup
trucks continue to outpace cars, parking lot designers, city
planners and even parking enforcement bureaus are scrambling to
deal with difficulties posed by these oversized vehicles. By Steve
Carney. (Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news
files.)
</P>
