 Saturday, Sept. 11, 1999   EDITORS:      The Hearst News Service will file the following story
for Sunday in the national and political categories (``a'' and
``p''):
<TEXT>
<P>
   NY-VIEQUES (New York) _ New York political leaders staged a City
Hall fact-finding hearing and a South Bronx rally Saturday to step
up political pressure on prospective U.S. Senate candidate Hillary
Rodham Clinton to oppose the Navy's use of the Puerto Rican island
of Vieques for target practice. By STEWART M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
