<P>
   RUSSIA-Y2K-$ADV12 _ MOSCOW _ Telephones on the blink. Bank cash
machines down. Government services crippled. Many Russians, all too
accustomed to things not working, would say it is just another day
in their faulty post-Soviet society. But Western experts predict
that the year 2000 computer problem could mean serious problems for
Russia, one of the least prepared of all industrialized nations to
cope with the Y2K bug. U.S. officials say the nuclear arsenal is
safe. The millennium is not going to touch off World War III. But
the extent to which the rest of life in Russia could be affected by
the bug is not fully known. (Holmes, Cox News Service). MOVED in
both International/financial categories.
</P>
