   (NYT8) SEATTLE -- Sept. 11, 1999 -- GATES-SENIOR-PROFILE-2,
09-11 -- William H. Gates Jr., co-chairman of the Gates Foundation,
with family photos at his home in Seattle. With more donations
expected, the Gates Foundation is virtually certain soon to surpass
the Wellcome Trust in Britain as the largest philanthropic
organization in the world. (Dan Lamont/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) SEATTLE -- Sept. 11, 1999 -- GATES-SENIOR-PROFILE-1,
09-11 -- William H. Gates Jr., 73, oversees the Gates Foundation,
his son's $17 billion philanthropy. Gates' philanthropic duties
with the foundation, for which he receives an annual salary of
$90,000, grew out of a conversation a few years ago with his son
and daughter-in-law during a night out at the movies. (Dan
Lamont/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) NEW YORK -- Sept. 11, 1999 -- TEN-USOPEN-6, 09-11 -- No.
3 seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia hits a backhand during his
semifinal match against No. 2 seed Andre Agassi of the United
States at the U.S. Open on Saturday. The winner will play for the
championship Sunday against Todd Martin, who defeated Cedric
Pioline in his semifinal. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) NEW YORK -- Sept. 11, 1999 -- TEN-USOPEN-5, 09-11 -- No.
2 seed Andre Agassi of the United States strikes a forehand during
his semifinal match against No. 3 seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia
at the U.S. Open on Saturday. The winner will play for the
championship Sunday against Todd Martin, who defeated Cedric
Pioline in his semifinal. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT4) NEW YORK -- Sept. 11, 1999 -- TEN-USOPEN-4, 09-11 -- No.
7 seed Todd Martin of the United States acknowledges the crowd
following his semifinal victory over unseeded Cedric Pioline of
France at the U.S. Open on Saturday. Martin won in straight sets,
6-4, 6-1, 6-2, and will play for the championship Sunday against
either Andre Agassi or Yevgeny Kafelnikov. (Chang W. Lee/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) NEW YORK -- Sept. 11, 1999 -- TEN-USOPEN-3, 09-11 -- No.
7 seed Todd Martin of the United States launches a serve during his
semifinal match against unseeded Cedric Pioline of France at the
U.S. Open on Saturday. Martin won, 6-4, 6-1, 6-2, and will play for
the championship Sunday against either Andre Agassi or Yevgeny
Kafelnikov. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) NEW YORK -- Sept. 11, 1999 -- TEN-USOPEN-2, 09-11 --
Unseeded Cedric Pioline of France conveys a look of disgust during
his match against No. 7 seed Todd Martin of the United States at
the U.S. Open on Saturday. The winner will play for the
championship Sunday against either Andre Agassi or Yevgeny
Kafelnikov. (Chang W. Lee/New York Times Photo)
