<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 
The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Sunday, Sept. 12. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
AMWEST-FAA _ The Federal Aviation Administration in Washington
waived a $2.5 million fine against America West Airlines in July
despite objections from the agency's Phoenix inspectors. America
West, slapped with a $5 million fine last year over safety and
maintenance violations, had not fully complied with an agreement to
fix the problems, according to the FAA inspectors in Phoenix who
oversee the airline. By PETER CORBETT. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
GAY-MILITARY _ Whether Steve May, a gay Arizona legislator, should
remain in the military reserves has been debated on national news
and talk shows. On Saturday, May taught military strategies to
reservists as a media pack looked on. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
WALMART _ Wal-Mart's plans to build at least 16 huge supercenter
stores in Arizona have transformed the state into the latest
battleground in the retailer's effort to barge into the nation's
grocery business. City governments, neighborhood groups and
grocery-union members are throwing blockades in front of Wal-Mart's
plans and killing off some of them. Story will move in the ``A''
and ``F'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
TV-GOODY (Undated) _ ``I know you mean well, but you really have to
let me grow up.''That's a line from a new television series this
fall. So what? you say. What precocious teen hasn't uttered the
same words to her parents? But that's just it _ it's not a teen who
says it. It's a grown woman. A mother herself. A judge, no less.
That pretty much sums up the new fall season. Think young,
attractive actors. Then chop a few years off what you're picturing.
Add a couple of levels of beauty, subtract a measure of maturity
and you've got the idea. By BILL GOODYKOONTZ. Story will move in
the ``E'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
